(GLASS BREAKING)

15:03.333 --> 15:04.500
(LAUGHS MANIACALLY)

15:05.367 --> 15:07.433
(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

15:10.400 --> 15:12.600
JONATHAN: The fabulous Xavier,
ladies and gentlemen.

15:12.667 --> 15:15.667
How great was that? <i>Magnifique!</i>

15:18.067 --> 15:19.400
We've had performers on stage here,

15:19.467 --> 15:20.833
and I think they're here
performing for us.

15:20.933 --> 15:23.867
Here I felt that we entered
your world, I really did.

15:23.933 --> 15:26.367
It was such a beautiful experience.
What inspires you?

15:26.433 --> 15:28.933
What is it that you're hoping to achieve
when you perform like that?

15:29.333 --> 15:35.000
Um, I was very much inspired
by physical comedy, and like,

15:35.067 --> 15:37.600
you know, Charlie Chaplin,
and this kind of things.

15:37.733 --> 15:42.367
So I tried to put some meanings
and, uh, story in my magic, so...

15:42.433 --> 15:44.000
It's a little bit of reward, yes.

15:44.067 --> 15:45.600
Well, let's go over to Penn, right now.

15:45.967 --> 15:50.033
A lot of people
don't know that film was really...

15:50.167 --> 15:54.400
Really pushed forward
by mostly French magicians.

15:54.467 --> 15:56.067
I mean, they were...
They were big on that.

15:56.133 --> 15:58.633
And you've continued that
with a great film-to-life.

15:58.833 --> 16:02.533
Yeah. I was very inspired
by Georges Méliès. I love his work.

16:02.667 --> 16:05.200
And if we had any doubt
about you truly being French,

16:05.267 --> 16:06.467
you proved it with the music.

16:06.600 --> 16:09.967
There's no doubt that,
that was French music.

16:10.033 --> 16:14.733
What you've also done
is just a classic storytelling fantasy,

16:14.900 --> 16:20.067
working all the way through,
and a film-to-life with an updated...

16:20.333 --> 16:22.900
And a very nice and, uh...

16:23.033 --> 16:25.433
Extensive handling

16:25.500 --> 16:28.767
of a daylight séance gimmick,
which you use beautifully.

16:28.867 --> 16:33.100
Just a wonderful, wonderful routine
that I just loved all the way through.

16:35.600 --> 16:39.200
So with Penn using those
phrases like "daylight séance,"

16:39.267 --> 16:41.767
which doesn't really mean
anything to the rest of us,

16:41.833 --> 16:43.667
but I guess you guys
are on the same page here.

16:43.733 --> 16:46.033
-They know what you were doing?
-Of course.

16:46.100 --> 16:47.200
(LAUGHING)

16:47.267 --> 16:50.167
So you didn't fool them,
but you gave us a great time.

16:50.233 --> 16:51.700
Xavier, ladies and gentlemen!

16:52.967 --> 16:54.800
Thank you, Xavier. Congratulations.

16:55.567 --> 16:57.133
(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

16:58.800 --> 17:02.167
For my own bit of magic,
watch as I conjure up our next contender.

17:06.200 --> 17:08.800
My name is Greg Dow.
I'm from Las Vegas, Nevada,

17:08.867 --> 17:11.400
and I'm a magician
that performs at corporate events,

17:11.467 --> 17:13.500
trade shows, and private parties.

17:13.666 --> 17:15.433
<i>I love close-up magic the best.</i>

17:15.532 --> 17:17.500
<i>I love seeing the look on people's faces</i>

17:17.567 --> 17:20.133
<i>when the magic happens</i>
<i>right in front of them.</i>

17:21.233 --> 17:25.367
<i>The thing about doing magic at corporate</i>
<i>events is, it's all very safe.</i>

17:26.267 --> 17:28.833
<i>Magic for people in suits and ties.</i>

17:29.367 --> 17:32.500
You have to make sure
you don't offend anyone.

17:32.567 --> 17:35.900
But sometimes,
the real me needs to come out.

17:36.233 --> 17:37.933
<i>So, I put on a mask,</i>

17:38.000 --> 17:42.100
<i>not to hide my identity,</i>
<i>but to unleash it!</i>

17:42.667 --> 17:45.867
And that's when I become The Shocker!

17:49.500 --> 17:51.733
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

17:52.967 --> 17:55.067
How brave of this next magician,

17:55.133 --> 17:58.333
performing right after his secret
identity was revealed to all of us.

17:58.400 --> 18:01.067
Please welcome my hero, The Shocker!

18:03.200 --> 18:06.000
Ladies and gentlemen, I am The Shocker!

18:06.833 --> 18:10.267
And that's what it looks like
when Spider-Man has alone time.

18:12.100 --> 18:17.433
I'm the world's best, and only,
pro-wrestling magician.

18:18.167 --> 18:20.900
Which means I'm the guy that's
gonna pretend to kick your ass

18:20.967 --> 18:23.567
as I pretend to do Harry Potter stuff.

18:25.133 --> 18:27.300
And this is a good-looking
audience tonight.

18:27.367 --> 18:29.367
-You guys are attractive!
-(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

18:30.967 --> 18:34.033
I'm gonna take the mask off
just so I can see you guys better.

18:37.400 --> 18:41.033
So tonight I am going
to attempt to read the minds

18:41.133 --> 18:43.000
of some of the members
of the audience here.

18:43.067 --> 18:46.067
Now, normally when I do this,
I have a tag-team partner,

18:46.133 --> 18:48.833
someone who knows
my every thought before I think it,

18:48.900 --> 18:50.567
my every move before I make it.

18:50.633 --> 18:53.533
Unfortunately,
he could not be here tonight.

18:54.867 --> 18:58.600
So instead, I brought
his mask along with me.

18:59.033 --> 19:03.667
Now, this mask was made
from the tiger that bit Roy.

19:03.833 --> 19:05.767
JONATHAN (CHUCKLING): Ooh.

19:05.933 --> 19:08.033
You hate that,
you're gonna hate my new rug.

19:09.200 --> 19:12.600
Now, I'm gonna toss this mask
out into the audience to a gentleman.

19:12.667 --> 19:14.300
He is gonna place it upon his head.

19:14.367 --> 19:17.367
That will allow me to have
a mental connection with this guy.

19:17.433 --> 19:20.167
I'm gonna go completely random here.

19:21.900 --> 19:24.867
Place the mask on, you'll get
the giant-est round of applause

19:24.933 --> 19:26.533
you've ever received in your life!

19:26.700 --> 19:28.700
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

19:31.567 --> 19:32.900
Now, here's what's gonna happen.

19:33.300 --> 19:34.933
I'm gonna ask you a question.

19:35.000 --> 19:38.100
You're gonna send me the answer
using the power of your mind.

19:38.233 --> 19:40.567
I'm gonna write it down.
We're gonna see how it went.

19:40.633 --> 19:44.267
Jonathan, if you would,
document our progress.

19:44.333 --> 19:45.800
-My pleasure.
-Perfect!

19:46.300 --> 19:51.133
Sir, if you would,
I want you to think of the name

19:51.433 --> 19:54.400
of a woman that is important in your life.

19:54.867 --> 19:57.633
But I don't want it to be
your mom or your sister,

19:58.067 --> 19:59.967
because I want it to be one I don't know.

20:00.300 --> 20:01.500
Oh!

20:02.267 --> 20:03.433
Shocker!

20:05.500 --> 20:06.667
Do you have the name?

20:06.900 --> 20:08.267
-Yes.
-Send it to me

20:08.333 --> 20:09.933
using the power of your mind.

20:11.100 --> 20:13.367
That's a pretty name. All right.
(GRUNTING)

20:14.800 --> 20:16.433
I'm gonna lock that down

20:16.933 --> 20:20.400
into envelope number one.

20:21.167 --> 20:23.300
Just like that, you guys
can see it going in.

20:23.367 --> 20:27.100
Let's peel this safety seal off.
That is locked in.

20:27.167 --> 20:29.833
For the first time,
for our record-keeper Jonathan,

20:30.033 --> 20:32.533
what is the name of the woman
you were thinking of?

20:32.867 --> 20:34.467
-Donna.
-Donna!

20:34.567 --> 20:35.933
-Donna.
-Please write down Donna.

20:36.000 --> 20:37.000
Donna.

20:37.200 --> 20:38.233
Take the mask.

20:38.533 --> 20:41.200
Toss it behind you to a young lady.

20:41.433 --> 20:43.767
There you go!
This young lady right here!

20:44.667 --> 20:47.633
You're gonna place the mask on your head,

20:47.833 --> 20:51.233
and I'm going to attempt
to read your mind.

20:51.867 --> 20:56.667
I want you to think of your
favorite thing to do with a man.

20:57.467 --> 20:58.467
(LAUGHTER)

20:59.100 --> 21:00.533
Send it to me.

21:02.567 --> 21:05.067
Interesting! All right.

21:05.933 --> 21:10.033
I am going to write down
what you have sent me,

21:10.333 --> 21:14.533
lock it in to envelope number two.

21:15.467 --> 21:19.667
Now, what do you like to do with a man?

21:19.933 --> 21:22.067
-Wrestle!
-SHOCKER: Wrestle!

21:22.533 --> 21:23.533
(APPLAUSE)

21:25.700 --> 21:26.800
JONATHAN: Well.

21:26.867 --> 21:30.267
Not what he was hoping
you were going to say, by the way.

21:30.600 --> 21:34.200
Toss the mask back up here, or give
it a little conga line on its way up.

21:34.400 --> 21:36.633
There we go, it's gonna toss...
It's gonna come over the...

21:37.067 --> 21:38.300
Perfect!

21:39.500 --> 21:41.133
(LAUGHTER)

21:42.067 --> 21:44.867
Now, since this is a magic competition...

21:46.367 --> 21:49.900
By Vegas law, I have to do
something with a deck of cards.

21:50.800 --> 21:53.533
So I'm gonna write down
what I think is going to happen

21:54.167 --> 21:55.867
with the cards here.

21:58.100 --> 22:00.633
Perfect! I have locked that in...

22:02.133 --> 22:04.133
To envelope number three.

22:04.800 --> 22:06.767
All the way in, sealed up.

22:07.733 --> 22:10.200
In there. I'm gonna
come out to Penn and Teller.

22:10.900 --> 22:12.233
If you would please, Teller,

22:13.000 --> 22:14.367
select a card.

22:17.133 --> 22:18.167
Perfect!

22:18.333 --> 22:21.167
For the first time, so Jonathan
can write it down, Teller,

22:21.233 --> 22:23.200
out loud, what card did you pick?

22:24.367 --> 22:27.700
Let me try that again.
Penn, for the first time,

22:27.767 --> 22:29.867
out loud for Jonathan,
what card did he pick?

22:30.533 --> 22:32.233
The three of clubs.

22:32.300 --> 22:33.367
JONATHAN: Three of clubs.

22:34.100 --> 22:35.167
Um...

22:36.267 --> 22:37.500
What was it again?

22:37.567 --> 22:39.167
PENN: The three of clubs.

22:39.233 --> 22:40.300
SHOCKER: Three of clubs.

22:41.133 --> 22:42.600
The end might suck.

22:44.267 --> 22:45.767
Let's take a look, though.
Let's go.

22:45.833 --> 22:47.400
First, we went to this guy right here,

22:47.600 --> 22:49.800
asked him the name
of a woman important in his life.

22:50.200 --> 22:52.467
Locked it into envelope number one.

22:52.667 --> 22:54.600
You said the name.
What did he say, Jonathan?

22:54.667 --> 22:55.700
He said Donna.

22:55.767 --> 22:58.033
Donna, and I wrote down the name.

22:58.733 --> 22:59.900
-Donna!
-(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

23:02.433 --> 23:05.067
And then we went to this young
lady right here,

23:05.133 --> 23:07.433
asked her favorite thing to do with a man.

23:07.500 --> 23:09.200
Locked it in envelope number two!

23:09.267 --> 23:11.133
She said she likes to...

23:11.200 --> 23:13.300
-Wrestle!
-She likes to wrestle.

23:13.500 --> 23:17.833
And I wrote down
that she likes to wrestle!

23:17.967 --> 23:19.433
(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

23:19.900 --> 23:23.133
And then, we went to Penn and Teller.

23:23.200 --> 23:24.300
PENN: Yes.

23:25.100 --> 23:26.867
You picked the three of clubs.

23:28.033 --> 23:30.833
Locked my prediction
into envelope number three.

23:31.400 --> 23:33.400
I wrote down the, um...

23:34.367 --> 23:35.433
Eight of diamonds.

23:35.833 --> 23:37.767
-AUDIENCE: Aw.
-Aw.

23:39.633 --> 23:41.633
Now, this is where it gets a little weird.

23:41.700 --> 23:44.933
I'm not sure how you messed that one up.

23:45.367 --> 23:46.700
(LAUGHTER)

23:46.933 --> 23:49.167
Because every card I gave you

23:50.067 --> 23:52.267
was the damn eight of diamonds!

23:53.800 --> 23:55.367
So how about,

23:55.533 --> 23:58.767
instead of you picking the wrong card,

23:59.800 --> 24:01.133
I fix the prediction

24:02.300 --> 24:03.933
to match the card you picked?

24:05.133 --> 24:06.233
Three of clubs?

24:07.000 --> 24:08.100
Three of clubs!

24:08.667 --> 24:10.400
AUDIENCE: (CHANTING)
Shocker! Shocker! Shocker!

24:10.467 --> 24:12.967
Ladies and gentlemen,
I'm The Shocker! Thank you!

24:13.133 --> 24:14.467
And good night!

24:15.733 --> 24:17.533
JONATHAN: The Shocker,
ladies and gentlemen.

24:17.733 --> 24:20.200
What a great finish.
Great style as well.

24:20.433 --> 24:24.100
Earlier, we saw you in your
Greg persona, the corporate magician.

24:24.300 --> 24:25.433
Now we're meeting The Shocker.

24:25.500 --> 24:28.967
The two personalities, they ever
get mixed up, do they ever clash on stage?

24:29.333 --> 24:32.467
Well, Greg had this girlfriend once...

24:32.567 --> 24:33.833
(LAUGHING)

24:34.900 --> 24:36.500
Are you ready to give us your verdict?

24:36.600 --> 24:37.967
The Shocker!

24:38.933 --> 24:42.600
Boy, I just love acts
that go right to the edge there.

24:42.667 --> 24:44.533
I will tell you, um,

24:44.600 --> 24:47.533
with changing from the eight of diamonds

24:47.600 --> 24:50.667
to the three of clubs,
you were one ahead of us there.

24:50.733 --> 24:53.033
But, I also will just say

24:53.467 --> 24:56.100
you probably don't want us to handle

24:56.467 --> 24:58.333
that prediction at the end.
Is that right?

24:58.400 --> 25:00.533
Well, I'm gonna say this.

25:00.600 --> 25:04.333
You're on the right track,
and you can finish that thought,

25:04.633 --> 25:07.533
or you can have the best damn
opening act you've ever had.

25:07.600 --> 25:09.167
(LAUGHTER)

25:09.533 --> 25:11.200
What do you guys think?

25:11.567 --> 25:14.633
AUDIENCE: (CHANTING)
Shocker! Shocker! Shocker!

25:16.100 --> 25:17.933
Are you happy?
You're confident that they kind of know

25:18.000 --> 25:19.133
what they're talking about there?

25:19.200 --> 25:20.833
I'm pretty sure these are smart guys here.

25:20.900 --> 25:23.733
So they've got it down.
But what a great performance.

25:23.800 --> 25:25.900
Wasn't he awesome, ladies and gentlemen?

25:26.500 --> 25:29.067
Let's hear it again for The Shocker!

25:29.200 --> 25:31.200
AUDIENCE: (CHANTING)
Shocker! Shocker! Shocker!

25:32.767 --> 25:35.433
So now let's learn
all about our next trickster.

25:40.133 --> 25:42.267
<i>Hi. My name is Steven Brundage.</i>
<i>I grew up in Brooklyn,</i>

25:42.333 --> 25:44.633
<i>but I currently live</i>
<i>in Saratoga Springs, New York.</i>

25:44.733 --> 25:46.433
Who here can actually solve
a Rubik's Cube?

25:46.500 --> 25:49.433
When I was a kid, I got a Rubik's Cube,
and I basically locked myself in a room

25:49.533 --> 25:50.867
<i>and I started to learn how to solve it.</i>

25:51.567 --> 25:54.600
<i>So I was doing magic for two years</i>
<i>full-time to make ends meet,</i>

25:54.667 --> 25:56.267
and then I had a viral video take off.

25:56.333 --> 25:58.633
<i>I was driving from a gig.</i>
<i>I got pulled over.</i>

25:58.867 --> 26:01.333
<i>I told the officer I was a magician,</i>

26:01.400 --> 26:02.933
so he asked to see a trick.

26:03.233 --> 26:05.133
<i>From mixed up, in one hand,</i>
<i>and behind the back.</i>

26:06.967 --> 26:08.500
<i>When I catch it again, take a look.</i>

26:08.567 --> 26:10.100
POLICEMAN: <i>Holy</i> (BEEP)

26:10.167 --> 26:13.067
The viral video took off.
I got 15 million views total.

26:13.133 --> 26:14.667
<i>Since then, things have kind of taken off,</i>

26:14.733 --> 26:17.333
<i>and I'm actually traveling</i>
<i>across the country to do gigs now.</i>

26:17.733 --> 26:18.833
(LAUGHING) Yes!

26:19.533 --> 26:21.567
I have a girlfriend now,
and she's kind of out of my league,

26:21.667 --> 26:22.867
but I think the magic helps a little bit.

26:22.933 --> 26:24.433
<i>I'm really excited to be on</i> Penn &amp; Teller.

26:24.533 --> 26:26.967
<i>Who knew so much could</i>
<i>happen from having a viral video?</i>

26:30.800 --> 26:33.267
Our next performer cut his
teeth as a street performer,

26:33.333 --> 26:34.933
so you might want
to get your loose change handy

26:35.000 --> 26:37.333
in case he passes around the hat
after what he's doing now.

26:37.400 --> 26:39.300
Please welcome Steven Brundage!

26:39.467 --> 26:41.467
(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

26:41.867 --> 26:43.533
Hi. Thank you so much for having me.

26:43.633 --> 26:46.500
Uh, I'm gonna do something
really awesome with two Rubik's Cubes.

26:46.667 --> 26:48.167
Um, I've always loved to solve it,

26:48.367 --> 26:49.867
but I'm gonna try something
with Penn and Teller.

26:49.933 --> 26:51.300
Can you guys join me up on stage, please?

26:51.367 --> 26:52.467
Thank you so much.

26:52.733 --> 26:53.733
(APPLAUSE)

26:54.900 --> 26:55.967
Nice meeting you.

26:57.067 --> 26:59.500
Nice to meet you, as well.
Thank you so much.

26:59.567 --> 27:00.700
Perfect. So we'll get started.

27:00.767 --> 27:01.967
So, Penn, I'm gonna need your help first.

27:02.033 --> 27:03.367
-We have two Rubik's Cubes.
-Okay.

27:03.433 --> 27:05.800
You can choose either one to mix up.
Your choice. It doesn't matter.

27:05.867 --> 27:08.100
-I'll take that one.
-Perfect. I want you to mix it up.

27:08.233 --> 27:10.600
Just like a deck of cards
is similar to a Rubik's Cube

27:10.667 --> 27:13.533
in the fashion that it takes seven
shuffles with a deck of cards

27:13.600 --> 27:15.033
before it's thoroughly randomized.

27:15.100 --> 27:17.233
A Rubik's Cube is actually 20 moves.

27:17.467 --> 27:19.867
So I want you to start to turn
and twist it up for me, please.

27:19.933 --> 27:22.567
And any time you want,
I want you to say the word, "Stop."

27:22.633 --> 27:24.700
When you say stop,
we're both gonna stop mixing for me.

27:24.800 --> 27:25.867
Okay.

27:27.167 --> 27:28.800
(LAUGHTER)

27:30.333 --> 27:31.333
Stop!

27:31.400 --> 27:32.400
-Right there.
-Yeah.

27:32.467 --> 27:34.067
Perfect. I'll take it back.
You said stop,

27:34.133 --> 27:37.200
and we both stopped mixing up
the Rubik's Cubes at the same, exact time.

27:37.267 --> 27:38.833
Teller, do you mind
helping me out next, please?

27:39.300 --> 27:41.167
Perfect. So we have two cubes here.

27:41.233 --> 27:42.567
I want you to choose either one.

27:42.667 --> 27:44.267
Go for it.
Whichever one you choose,

27:44.500 --> 27:45.800
you're gonna hold it in your hand,

27:45.867 --> 27:47.767
and when you open up,
it's gonna be solved.

27:50.100 --> 27:52.033
Perfect.
So cover it up for me.

27:53.067 --> 27:54.133
Perfect. Watch.

27:58.000 --> 27:59.467
It's now solved.
Take a look.

27:59.533 --> 28:00.700
Is it solved?

28:01.300 --> 28:02.633
That would have been amazing, though.

28:02.700 --> 28:03.933
It would have been great, yeah.

28:04.967 --> 28:07.733
Can you picture the Rubik's Cube
one move away from being solved?

28:07.967 --> 28:09.033
Uh, barely.

28:09.100 --> 28:11.333
Barely. I'll give you a hint.
So that's basically one move away.

28:11.400 --> 28:13.867
There's two, three, four...
The more you mix it up,

28:13.967 --> 28:15.367
the harder the patterns on the cube

28:15.433 --> 28:16.667
-are gonna be to recognize.
-Right.

28:16.733 --> 28:20.133
We're gonna mix it up to about
20 moves away, then go back in time.

28:20.200 --> 28:22.000
So picture the Rubik's Cube
at 20 moves away.

28:22.067 --> 28:23.467
Imagine in your mind

28:23.533 --> 28:27.367
if the Rubik's Cube is maybe only
10 moves away from being mixed up.

28:27.433 --> 28:29.733
Picture at seven
what you're gonna see with the cube.

28:29.800 --> 28:31.800
Imagine if the Rubik's Cube
is only one move away,

28:31.867 --> 28:33.900
then finally, in your mind,
when it's completely solved,

28:33.967 --> 28:35.000
let me know when you see it.

28:35.067 --> 28:37.000
-It's completely solved.
-Just like that?

28:37.233 --> 28:38.767
-Thank you.
-Yeah.

28:40.267 --> 28:43.467
Yeah, that was good, but this time,
I'm actually gonna solve the Rubik's Cube.

28:43.533 --> 28:45.900
This time, I'm gonna use
a paper bag that I have down here.

28:47.033 --> 28:48.967
I want you to watch
all the different sides of the cube.

28:49.033 --> 28:50.967
You can see there's no patterns
or big blocks on the cube,

28:51.033 --> 28:52.367
so you know it's thoroughly mixed up.

28:52.433 --> 28:54.167
I want you to watch.
We're gonna place it in the bag.

28:54.233 --> 28:56.067
This is the coolest part of the show.

28:56.367 --> 28:57.633
Is it still mixed up in there?

28:57.733 --> 28:59.667
-Uh, yes, it is.
-Still mixed up. Still mixed up?

28:59.900 --> 29:01.067
Watch.

29:02.367 --> 29:03.533
It's now solved.

29:03.733 --> 29:05.333
Well, that's great.
I don't believe you.

29:05.400 --> 29:07.167
You don't. Okay.
No, I'll prove it. Hands empty.

29:07.233 --> 29:09.267
I want you to watch.
As slowly as possible.

29:09.667 --> 29:12.967
That is one solved Rubik's Cube
and one empty bag.

29:13.500 --> 29:15.467
-Thank you.
-(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

29:20.033 --> 29:21.400
Now, here's the thing.
As a kid,

29:21.467 --> 29:23.600
I used to actually go
to these speed-solving competitions,

29:23.667 --> 29:26.333
and I would sit there and I would
always race, but I could never win,

29:26.433 --> 29:27.667
so I had to cheat.

29:27.800 --> 29:29.867
